((3) 0 () 0 () () (u . "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <meta name=\"format-detection\" content=\"telephone=no\">\n\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/functions.js\"></script>\n\n  <meta content=\"Colophon | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" name=\"title\" />\n  <meta content=\"A note, traditionally found at the end of a book, describing the typefaces, tools, and methods used in its\nproduction.\" name=\"description\" />\n  <meta content=\"website\" property=\"og:type\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/colophon.html\" property=\"og:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Colophon | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"og:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"A note, traditionally found at the end of a book, describing the typefaces, tools, and methods used in its\nproduction.\" property=\"og:description\" />\n  <meta content=\"summary_large_image\" property=\"twitter:card\" />\n  <meta content=\"@xandernn\" property=\"twitter:site\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/colophon.html\" property=\"twitter:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Colophon | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"twitter:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"A note, traditionally found at the end of a book, describing the typefaces, tools, and methods used in its\nproduction.\" property=\"twitter:description\" />\n\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/fonts/fonts.css\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/styles.css\" />\n\n  <title>Colophon | Alexander Nabavi-Noori</title>\n\n  <style type=\"text/css\">\n    #switcher {\n      margin-top: 12px;\n      border: 1px solid gray;\n      box-shadow: 2px 2px;\n      cursor: default;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding-top: 0.2em;\n      padding-bottom: 0.2em;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n\n<body id=\"body\" class=\"body-text_century-supra\">\n\n  <div id=\"switcher\"><a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"index.html\">About</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"research.html\">Research</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"experience.html\">Experience</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"blog.html\">Blog</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"ANabaviNoori_CV.pdf\">CV</a>\n</div>\n\n  <div id=\"content\">\n\n    <div id=\"doc\"><div id=\"doc\"><p><title-block><topic class=\"small\">Colophon</topic><short-rule>A note, tra\u00ADdi\u00ADtion\u00ADally found at the end of a book, describ\u00ADing the type\u00ADfaces, tools, and meth\u00ADods used in its<br/>pro\u00ADduc\u00ADtion.</short-rule></title-block></p><p>This web\u00ADsite’s design is based on the web\u00ADsites of Matthew But\u00ADt\u00ADer\u00ADick—in par\u00ADtic\u00ADu\u00ADlar <a href=\"https://practicaltypography.com\"><book>Prac\u00ADti\u00ADcal Typog\u00ADra\u00ADphy</book></a> and <a href=\"https://typographyforlawyers.com\"><book>Typog\u00ADra\u00ADphy for Lawyers</book></a>—whose text-first, read\u00ADable approach to web design has shaped how I think about pre\u00ADsent\u00ADing words on a screen. It is built with <a href=\"https://github.com/mattbutterick/pollen\">Pollen,</a> an open-source pub\u00ADlish\u00ADing sys\u00ADtem also by But\u00ADt\u00ADer\u00ADick. But\u00ADt\u00ADer\u00ADick’s writ\u00ADing on typog\u00ADra\u00ADphy and type\u00ADset\u00ADting has been a quiet influ\u00ADence on my work as a law\u00ADyer for years, and I’m grate\u00ADful for it.</p><p>The fonts used on this site are all designed by But\u00ADt\u00ADer\u00ADick and avail\u00ADable through his foundry, <a href=\"https://mbtype.com\">MB Type.</a></p><ol><li><p>Cen\u00ADtury Supra is the main body text font through\u00ADout the site.</p></li><li><p><span class=\"font-equity\">Equity</span>, <span class=\"font-concourse-c4\">Con\u00ADcourse</span>, <span class=\"font-triplicate\">Trip\u00ADli\u00ADcate</span>, <span class=\"font-advocate-c43\">Advo\u00ADcate</span>, and <span class=\"font-heliotrope\">Heliotrope</span> appear in sup\u00ADport\u00ADing roles.</p></li></ol><p>More about But\u00ADt\u00ADer\u00ADick’s fonts and his approach to typog\u00ADra\u00ADphy can be found at <a href=\"https://practicaltypography.com\">prac\u00ADti\u00ADcal\u00ADty\u00ADpog\u00ADra\u00ADphy.com.</a></p></div></div><a id=\"links\"></a>\n    <div class=\"gap\" style=\"height:1em\"></div>\n    <ul class=\"children\"></ul>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"toolbar\" class=\"\">\n\n    <div id=\"navtable\">\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"colophon.html\"><span class=\"arrow\">←</span>&nbsp;colophon</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"center\">\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/\">home</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/ANabaviNoori_CV.pdf\">curriculum vitae&nbsp;<span class=\"arrow\">→</span></a>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n</body>\n\n</html>"))